## <a id="1-7-1"></a> v1.7.1

**Release Date: August 9, 2022**

### New Features

- Update stacks

### Breaking Changes

None

### Product Snapshot

Tanzu Build Service 1.7.1 ships with the following components:

* [kpack 0.6.1](https://github.com/pivotal/kpack/releases/tag/v0.6.1)
* [kpack cli v0.6.0](https://github.com/vmware-tanzu/kpack-cli/releases/tag/v0.6.0)
* [CNB lifecycle v0.14.1](https://github.com/buildpacks/lifecycle/releases/tag/v0.14.1)

Tanzu Build Service supports and utilizes [Tanzu Buildpacks](https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-Tanzu-Buildpacks/index.html).

### Security Scanning

No HIGH or CRITICAL CVEs at time of release

### Product Dependencies

Build Service can be installed on any Kubernetes cluster (v1.19 or later).

### Upgrade Path

v1.5.* can be upgraded to v1.7.*. Please follow the [install](installing.html) process to upgrade.

### Deprecated Features

* The (legacy) CNB BOM format is deprecated, but enabled by default in TBS. Support can be disabled manually by passing
`--data-value-yaml include_legacy_bom=false` to `ytt` when processing the TBS bundle or by adding
`include_legacy_bom=false` to your `tbs-values.yml` file.

